sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J100002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Suppressor tRNA CGGUC (K199028) is produced under regulation by the lpp promoter (K199106). The tRNA does not suppresses either of the frameshift mutations in Cre, causing Cre to be frameshifted and nonfunctional. We used this part as a control.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Eric Sawyer

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: p(tetR)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Lutz, R., Bujard, H., Nucleic Acids Research (1997) 25, 1203-1210.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sequence for pTet inverting regulator driven by the TetR protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_R0040 TetR-Regulated Promoter is based on a cI promoter. It has been modified to include two TetR binding sites and the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J100000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Cre with 8bp restriction sites and 1-Clause 2-SAT Problem Inserted
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Cre recombines DNA at lox sites (J61046). After the start codon is an AsiSI site, followed by a SAT problem, followed by an AscI site. If the tRNA K199002 OR the tRNA K199001 is expressed in the cell, then Cre is read in-frame. If neither tRNA is expressed, then Cre is frameshifted.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Eric Sawyer

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K199028
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: De Novo synthesis from oligos. Based on the paper by Anderson et al. (http://gcat.davidson.edu/GcatWiki/images/6/6f/AndersonSchultz2002ChemBiol.pdf)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This gene encodes for a 5 base pair tRNA suppressor that suppresses CGGUC, which would normally cause a frame shift mutation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We used the 9 base anticodon loop that is complementary to the 5 base pair codon CGGUC.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Alyndria Thompson

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K199106
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence matches that naturally found in E. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The lpp promoter is one of the strongest promoters in E. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Mary Gearing
